{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"p5vi6pdpl4wwk418shzymb6","title":"Docker","desc":"","updated":1657668785147,"created":1640494427533,"custom":{},"fname":"computer.docker","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"notes"},"contentHash":"ce6f236eda372fc123052291ad271ab7","links":[{"from":{"fname":"computer.frappe-framework","id":"enjb2w7wdyo2wyg7ek23500","vaultName":"notes"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":37,"column":1,"offset":1126},"end":{"line":37,"column":36,"offset":1161},"indent":[]},"value":"computer.docker"},{"from":{"fname":"computer.linux.debian","id":"qfhatiojg542x6a4yprmtz8","vaultName":"notes"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":5,"offset":289},"end":{"line":26,"column":24,"offset":308},"indent":[]},"value":"computer.docker"},{"from":{"fname":"computer.linux.debian","id":"qfhatiojg542x6a4yprmtz8","vaultName":"notes"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1,"offset":883},"end":{"line":42,"column":55,"offset":937},"indent":[]},"value":"computer.docker"}],"anchors":{"definition":{"type":"header","text":"Definition","value":"definition","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"dockerfiles":{"type":"header","text":"Dockerfiles","value":"dockerfiles","line":9,"column":0,"depth":2},"images":{"type":"header","text":"Images","value":"images","line":11,"column":0,"depth":2},"container":{"type":"header","text":"Container","value":"container","line":14,"column":0,"depth":2},"install":{"type":"header","text":"Install","value":"install","line":17,"column":0,"depth":1},"ubuntu-server":{"type":"header","text":"Ubuntu Server","value":"ubuntu-server","line":18,"column":0,"depth":2},"wsl-setup":{"type":"header","text":"WSL setup","value":"wsl-setup","line":21,"column":0,"depth":2},"add-user--post-install-setup":{"type":"header","text":"Add User / Post Install Setup","value":"add-user--post-install-setup","line":26,"column":0,"depth":3},"operations":{"type":"header","text":"Operations","value":"operations","line":31,"column":0,"depth":2},"list-all-containers":{"type":"header","text":"List all containers","value":"list-all-containers","line":32,"column":0,"depth":3},"filters":{"type":"header","text":"Filters","value":"filters","line":35,"column":0,"depth":3},"stop-all-containers":{"type":"header","text":"Stop all containers","value":"stop-all-containers","line":38,"column":0,"depth":3},"start-a-container":{"type":"header","text":"Start a container","value":"start-a-container","line":41,"column":0,"depth":3},"restart-policy":{"type":"header","text":"Restart Policy","value":"restart-policy","line":44,"column":0,"depth":3},"startup-behaviour":{"type":"header","text":"Startup Behaviour","value":"startup-behaviour","line":51,"column":0,"depth":3},"remove-all-containers":{"type":"header","text":"Remove all containers","value":"remove-all-containers","line":58,"column":0,"depth":3},"open-terminal-inside-running-container":{"type":"header","text":"Open terminal inside running container","value":"open-terminal-inside-running-container","line":61,"column":0,"depth":3},"copy-files-tofrom-volume":{"type":"header","text":"Copy files to/from volume","value":"copy-files-tofrom-volume","line":64,"column":0,"depth":3},"update-all-images":{"type":"header","text":"Update all images","value":"update-all-images","line":72,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":[],"parent":"67vcv6zhh0cxazsfqlaai29","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"docker\">Docker<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#docker\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"definition\">Definition<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#definition\"></a></h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://phoenixnap.com/kb/docker-image-vs-container\">Image vs Container</a>  </p>\n<h2 id=\"dockerfiles\">Dockerfiles<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#dockerfiles\"></a></h2>\n<p>Dockerfiles are a set of commands to build an image. Each command in a dockerfile adds a layer to an image.</p>\n<h2 id=\"images\">Images<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#images\"></a></h2>\n<p>Images are immutable snapshots of the current state, and are stored in an arbitrary number of layers.\nImages are required to run a container, and are obtained from a source like Docker hub or built with a Dockerfile.</p>\n<h2 id=\"container\">Container<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#container\"></a></h2>\n<p>A container refers to the environment where image layers and a read/write layer exist to run an application.</p>\n<h1 id=\"install\">Install<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#install\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"ubuntu-server\">Ubuntu Server<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#ubuntu-server\"></a></h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/ubuntu/#install-using-the-repository\">Link</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"wsl-setup\">WSL setup<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#wsl-setup\"></a></h2>\n<p>Ensure docker desktop is up to date<br>\nwsl2 selected in docker desktop<br>\nubuntu installed, instance enabled in docker desktop  </p>\n<h3 id=\"add-user--post-install-setup\">Add User / Post Install Setup<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#add-user--post-install-setup\"></a></h3>\n<pre><code>sudo groupadd docker\nsudo usermod -aG docker $USER\nnewgrp docker\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"operations\">Operations<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#operations\"></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"list-all-containers\">List all containers<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#list-all-containers\"></a></h3>\n<pre><code>docker ps -a\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"filters\">Filters<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#filters\"></a></h3>\n<pre><code>docker ps --filter \"name=TEST*\" \n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"stop-all-containers\">Stop all containers<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#stop-all-containers\"></a></h3>\n<pre><code>docker stop $(docker ps -aq)\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"start-a-container\">Start a container<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#start-a-container\"></a></h3>\n<pre><code>docker start CONTAINER [commands]\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"restart-policy\">Restart Policy<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#restart-policy\"></a></h3>\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<table><thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>no</td><td>Don't restart</td></tr><tr><td>on-failure[:max:retries]</td><td>restart if error only. retries option is optional.</td></tr><tr><td>unless-stopped</td><td>Like always except not if daemon restarts</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3 id=\"startup-behaviour\">Startup Behaviour<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#startup-behaviour\"></a></h3>\n<p>Prevent single container from starting on boot\ndocker update --restart=no   mycontainer</p>\n<p>Prevent all containers from starting on boot\ndocker update --restart=no $(docker ps -aq)</p>\n<h3 id=\"remove-all-containers\">Remove all containers<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#remove-all-containers\"></a></h3>\n<pre><code>docker rm $(docker ps -aq)\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"open-terminal-inside-running-container\">Open terminal inside running container<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#open-terminal-inside-running-container\"></a></h3>\n<pre><code>docker exec -it CONTAINER bash\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"copy-files-tofrom-volume\">Copy files to/from volume<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#copy-files-tofrom-volume\"></a></h3>\n<p><strong>Mount volume in container as shown but reverse the cp arguments to copy from host to container</strong>\ndocker run \\<br>\n-v VOLUME:/dir \\<br>\n--name copier -d hello-world \\<br>\ndocker cp copier:/dif/path /home/PATH<br>\ndocker rm copier  </p>\n<h3 id=\"update-all-images\">Update all images<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#update-all-images\"></a></h3>\n<p>docker images | grep -v ^REPO | sed 's/ +/:/g' | cut -d: -f1,2 | xargs -L1 docker pull</p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/enjb2w7wdyo2wyg7ek23500\">Frappe Framework</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/qfhatiojg542x6a4yprmtz8\">Debian</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"398cceh65hemaonxc6w22r7","title":"rodun","desc":"","updated":1673033072132,"created":1668995545797,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"notes"},"contentHash":"194939704b23314011141116733dafdb","links":[],"anchors":{"links":{"type":"header","text":"Links","value":"links","line":7,"column":0,"depth":2},"github":{"type":"header","text":"GitHub","value":"github","line":8,"column":0,"depth":3},"linkedin":{"type":"header","text":"LinkedIn","value":"linkedin","line":9,"column":0,"depth":3},"frappe-forum":{"type":"header","text":"Frappe Forum","value":"frappe-forum","line":10,"column":0,"depth":3},"hackerrank":{"type":"header","text":"HackerRank","value":"hackerrank","line":11,"column":0,"depth":3},"youtube":{"type":"header","text":"YouTube","value":"youtube","line":12,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":["ifoa0v25wh8cu1hxwdr9h42","5u88syeac813rvqauto8x7o","nc02voic3g7pn9o0vu5lyki","67vcv6zhh0cxazsfqlaai29","44oijwqa5kph6kobar7jckg","dcbhrrtovhg5rzaathh1vzo","15dblq3xeghfzhf4xy84qol","iyj5r87cpjx65khycaiepqo","zn57yzyn4u8t0upnvhlhh86","au5edemlol3d2awpbv9v95j","hjz2keujzwyj7ts555cxr3d","wn2fr0o5xhabmh5vfkevsvj","58xds0229zowl3885oqf38y"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"## Links\n### [GitHub](https://github.com/Robproject)\n### [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/rodun/)\n### [Frappe Forum](https://discuss.frappe.io/u/roberp/summary)\n### [HackerRa